{"lemma":"لَعْبُ","slug":"لَعْبُ","root":"ل.ع.ب","root_slug":"ل-ع-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ل-ع-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"لَعْبُ","root":"لعب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":8},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":10,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":15},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n37779","n37783","n37784","n37785","n37786"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%84%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to play","examples":[{"text":"الْأَطْفَالُ يَلْعَبُونَ فِي الْحَدِيقَةِ مَعَ أَصْدِقَائِهِم.","english":"The children play in the park with their friends."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to trick, to cheat"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cause to play, to set in motion"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to wag"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of لَعَبَ (laʕaba) (form I)","tags":["collective","form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"game","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sport, amusement, diversion","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of لَعِبَ (laʕiba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of لَعِبَ (laʕiba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of لَعِبَ (laʕiba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"funny, amusing"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of لُعْبَة (luʕba, “toy”)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to slobber, to drool"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of لَعَبَ (laʕaba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of لَعِبَ (laʕiba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/la.ʕi.ba/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n37779","headword_ar":"لَعِبَ","root":"lEb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laEibN","text_ar":"لَعِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(which is the original [and most common] form, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liEobN","text_ar":"لِعْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K: the latter of these inf. ns. contracted from the former, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laEobN","text_ar":"لَعْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K: also contracted from the first: not heard by IKt; but authorized by Mekkee, and, accord. to him,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2662},{"kind":"text","text":"agreeable with a constant rule, applicable in the case of any word of a similar measure having a guttural letter as its medial radical, whether a noun or verb: (TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uloEuwbapN","text_ar":"اُلْعُوبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taloEaAbN","text_ar":"تَلْعَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K; but this last has an intensive, or a frequentative, signification; S;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lE~b","text_ar":"لعّب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tlE~b","text_ar":"تلعّب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K: but this last has a frequentative [or an intensive] signification; S; [and so too has that immediately preceding it;]) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tlAEb","text_ar":"تلاعب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He played, sported, gamed, jested,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"joked: contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~a","text_ar":"جَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which signifies “ he was serious, or in earnest. ” (K.) [You say]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayonahumo A^uloEuwbapN","text_ar":"بَيْنَهُمْ اُلْعُوبَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Between them is playing, sporting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) [And so] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laAEabahaA","text_ar":"لَاعَبَهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mulaAEabapN","text_ar":"مُلَاعَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liEaAbN","text_ar":"لِعَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He played, sported, gamed, jested,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"joked, with her:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he toyed, dallied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wantoned, with her:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laAEabotu Alr~ajula","text_ar":"لَاعَبْتُ الرَّجُلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mlAEbp","text_ar":"ملاعبة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I played, &c., with the man."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laEibati Alr~iyHu biAlmanozili","text_ar":"لَعِبَتِ الرِّيحُ بِالمَنْزِلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"talaAEabat","text_ar":"تَلَاعَبَت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The wind sported with the lighting-place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of abode"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obliterated the traces of it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laEiba","text_ar":"لَعِبَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"binaA Almawoju","text_ar":"بِنَا المَوْجُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The waves sported with us"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: the commotion of the waves is called “ sporting ” because it does not convey the voyagers to the quarter whither they desire to go. (TA, from a trad.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laEaba","text_ar":"لَعَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laEiba","text_ar":"لَعِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laEobN","text_ar":"لَعْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEb","text_ar":"العب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a child, S)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slavered; drivelled; emitted a flow of slaver"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drivel from his mouth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) The first word is the most approved: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~abiY~u","text_ar":"الصَّبِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEb","text_ar":"العب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the child became slavering,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drivelling."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n37783","headword_ar":"لَعْبٌ","root":"lEb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalobN","text_ar":"عَلْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see the latter."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n37784","headword_ar":"لِعْبٌ","root":"lEb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laEibN","text_ar":"لَعِبٌ"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n37785","headword_ar":"لَعِبٌ","root":"lEb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liEibN","text_ar":"لِعِبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(with two kesrehs, agreeably with a constant rule obtaining in cases of this kind, [whereby the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEilN","text_ar":"فَعِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiEilN","text_ar":"فِعِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the medial radical letter being a guttural,] TA, [but in the CK and a MS. copy, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liEobN","text_ar":"لِعْبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is also regularly changed from the first,]) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uloEubaAnN","text_ar":"اُلْعُبَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luEabapN","text_ar":"لُعَبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luEobapN","text_ar":"لُعْبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, as from the K, [but not found by me in any copy of the latter work,]) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tiloEiybapN","text_ar":"تِلْعِيبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tiloEaAbN","text_ar":"تِلْعَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tiloEaAbapN","text_ar":"تِلْعَابَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taloEaAbN","text_ar":"تَلْعَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taloEaAbapN","text_ar":"تَلْعَابَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tiliE~aAbN","text_ar":"تِلِعَّابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tiliE~aAbapN","text_ar":"تِلِعَّابَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K: the last like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tiliq~aAmapN","text_ar":"تِلِقَّامَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is added to give [additional] intensiveness to the signification, as in the cases of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eal~aAmapN","text_ar":"عَلَّامَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nas~aAbapN","text_ar":"نَسَّابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": it is also used by En-Nábighah El-Jaadee in the place of an inf. n.: TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laEuwbN","text_ar":"لَعُوبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is common to both genders] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laE~aAbN","text_ar":"لَعَّابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, &c.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One who plays, sports, games, jests,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"jokes, much,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"often; a great player, sporter, &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.)"}],"source_refs":["K","S"]},{"entry_id":"n37786","headword_ar":"لِعِبٌ","root":"lEb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laEibN","text_ar":"لَعِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}